\begin_layout Standard
We now consider the case of two bubbles on the same trail.
 The temperature distribution on the two bubbles in this case is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
g_{1}(T) & =B_{1}\cos\theta+B_{2}\sin\theta\cos\phi\\
g_{2}(T) & =B_{1}\cos\theta-B_{2}\sin\theta\cos\phi
\end{align}

\end_inset

The force per unit area on the two bubbles is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
f_{\theta}^{1}(T) & =-B_{1}\sin\theta+B_{2}\cos\theta\cos\phi,\\
 & f_{\phi}^{1}(T)=-B_{2}\cos\theta\sin\phi\\
f_{\theta}^{2}(T) & =-B_{1}\sin\theta-B_{2}\cos\theta\cos\phi\\
 & f_{\phi}^{2}(T)=B_{2}\cos\theta\sin\phi
\end{align}

